THE FAIR VALUE AS OF THE VESTING DATE OF RSUS WAS $1 BILLION, $221 MILLION AND $320 MILLION FOR

2010, 2009 AND 2008, RESPECTIVELY. UPON VESTING, THE RSUS ARE GENERALLY NET SHARE-SETTLED TO COVER THE REQUIRED WITHHOLDING TAX AND THE REMAINING AMOUNT IS CONVERTED INTO AN EQUIVALENT NUMBER OF SHARES OF COMMON STOCK. THE MAJORITY OF RSUS THAT

VESTED IN 2010, 2009 AND 2008, WERE NET-SHARE SETTLED SUCH THAT THE COMPANY WITHHELD SHARES WITH VALUE EQUIVALENT TO THE EMPLOYEES MINIMUM STATUTORY OBLIGATION FOR THE APPLICABLE INCOME AND OTHER EMPLOYMENT TAXES, AND REMITTED THE CASH TO THE

APPROPRIATE TAXING AUTHORITIES. THE TOTAL SHARES WITHHELD WERE APPROXIMATELY 1.8 MILLION, 707,000 AND 857,000 FOR 2010, 2009 AND 2008, RESPECTIVELY, AND WERE BASED ON THE VALUE OF THE RSUS ON THEIR VESTING DATE AS DETERMINED BY THE

COMPANYS CLOSING STOCK PRICE. TOTAL PAYMENTS FOR THE EMPLOYEES TAX OBLIGATIONS TO THE TAXING AUTHORITIES WERE $406 MILLION, $82 MILLION AND $124 MILLION IN 2010, 2009 AND 2008, RESPECTIVELY, AND ARE REFLECTED AS A FINANCING ACTIVITY

WITHIN THE CONSOLIDATED STATEMENTS OF CASH FLOWS. THESE NET-SHARE SETTLEMENTS HAD THE EFFECT OF SHARE REPURCHASES BY THE COMPANY AS THEY REDUCED AND RETIRED THE NUMBER OF SHARES THAT WOULD HAVE OTHERWISE BEEN ISSUED AS A RESULT OF THE VESTING

AND DID NOT REPRESENT AN EXPENSE TO THE COMPANY.

